titlestmt.titleproper: Register to the Earl Banquer Collection
titlestmt.author: Compiled by Kendall L. Crilly

did.physdesc: (6 boxes)
did.abstract: Music for woodwind ensemble, arranged by or composed for Earl Banquer.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Earl Banquer Collection was established in the Music Library of Yale University by Earl Banquer in 2000.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The collection is open to researchers by appointment. There are no restricted materials in the collection. Please contact the Special Collections staff to schedule an appointment. Photocopies of materials in this collection are available directly from Mr. Banquer, 19 Beechwood Place, New Haven, CT 06511.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The Earl Banquer is the physical property of the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University. Copyrights belong to the composers and authors, or their legal heirs and assigns.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: MSS 80, The Earl Banquer Collection in the Irving S. Gilmore Music Library of Yale University.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Earl M. Banquer is an American clarinetist and musical arranger.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Earl Banquer Collection consists chiefly of Banquer's original musical arrangements of numerous classical and folk pieces, arranged for flute, 3 clarinets, and bass clarinet. The Collection also holds works commissioned by Banquer from Thomas Duffy, Michael Horvit, Collier Jones, and Yehudi Wyner.
